ActivityLog_RP (NEW)
Purpose: Tracks and stores statistics about mindfulness activities.
Responsibilities:

Track how many times each activity type was completed
Track total time spent in all mindfulness activities
Save statistics to a file after each activity
Load saved statistics when the program starts
Display statistics on demand


----------------------------------------------------
|             ActivityLog_RP                        |
----------------------------------------------------
| - _filename_RP : string                          |
| - _breathingCount_RP : int                       |
| - _reflectionCount_RP : int                      |
| - _listingCount_RP : int                         |
| - _totalTimeSpent_RP : int                       |
----------------------------------------------------
| + ActivityLog_RP()                               |
| + LogActivity_RP(name, duration)                 |
| + DisplayStats_RP()                              |
| - SaveStats_RP()                                 |
| - LoadStats_RP()                                 |
--------------------------------------------------



Program Flow Description

1. Show Main Menu
The program repeatedly shows this menu:

   Breathing Activity
   Reflection Activity
   Listing Activity
   View Statistics
   Quit

2. Start an Activity
   User selects an activity (1, 2, or 3)
   Program creates the corresponding activity object
   Program calls RunActivity_RP() on that object
   The activity displays a welcome message and asks for duration
   The activity runs for the specified time
   When finished, the activity logs itself via ActivityLog_RP
     (logs the activity name and duration spent)

3. View Statistics
   User selects option 4
   Program calls DisplayStats_RP() on the ActivityLog_RP object
   Displays:
     - Number of Breathing activities completed
     - Number of Reflection activities completed
     - Number of Listing activities completed
     - Total number of activities
     - Total time spent in mindfulness (in minutes and seconds)
   Waits for user to press Enter, then returns to main menu

4. Quit
   User selects option 5
   Statistics are automatically saved to file
   Program exits

5. Data Persistence
   When the program starts, ActivityLog_RP loads statistics from file
   After each activity completes, statistics are saved to file
   File format: four lines containing integers
     Line 1: Breathing count
     Line 2: Reflection count
     Line 3: Listing count
     Line 4: Total time in seconds